<p class="MsoNormal">Dear OMPI Developers,<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">I have put Mellanox OpenSHMEM up for review on my Bitbucket. Please &#8220;git&#8221; and test at your leisure. Questions, comments, and critiques are most welcome.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:black">git clone
<a href="https://bitbucket.org/jladd_math/mlnx-oshmem.git" title="https://bitbucket.org/jladd_math/mlnx-oshmem.git">
https://jladd_math@bitbucket.org/jladd_math/mlnx-oshmem.git</a></span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">To build with OSHMEM support, build as you would OMPI but simply include &#8216;--with-oshmem&#8217; on your configure line. This will get you started.
<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
